# Skill folder layout

Every pipeline skill uses this layout — same folder names and roles:

```
.cursor/skills/<skill>/
├── SKILL.md
├── indexes/          # reference-index.md, topic-pointer-index.md
├── protocol/         # pipeline-commands, repository-scripts-map, environment-variables, agent-runtime
├── notion/           # tracker-schema.md, mcp-workflows.md
├── contracts/        # data-formats.md, run-log-template.md
├── domain/           # skill-unique knowledge only
├── assets/           # application-filler only (PII + resume)
├── logs/
└── scripts/setup.sh
```

## SKILL.md skeleton

1. YAML frontmatter: `name`, `description`, `disable-model-invocation: true`
2. Title + orchestration runbook line + link to `indexes/reference-index.md`
3. Phase checklist
4. Numbered `## N.` sections with `→` links into classified folders or `docs/shared/`
5. No links to other skills

## Do not

- Invent alternate top-level folders for the same concerns
- Put shared policy inside a skill — use `docs/shared/`
- Add `assets/` to skills other than application-filler
- Cross-link another skill’s files
